properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 4 at 2:05AM EST until January 5 at 11:00AM EST by NWS Wakefield VA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 25 to 30 kt with gusts to 35 to 40 kt.
Seas 4 to 7 ft.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Fenwick Island DE to Chincoteague
VA out 20 nm, Coastal waters from Chincoteague to Parramore
Island VA out 20 nm, Coastal waters from Parramore Island to
Cape Charles Light VA out 20 nm, Coastal Waters from Cape
Charles Light to Virginia-North Carolina border out to 20 nm
and Coastal waters from NC VA border to Currituck Beach Light
NC out 20 nm.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 11 AM EST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 11 AM EST SUNDAY
